  <span id="freeText3166211136602804477" style="display:none">The diary format lends itself well to the tales of these interns, whose stories are equal parts inspiring, exhausting and invigorating. I read this as a senior in high school and it didn't scare me off from pursuing a Pre-Med track in college. What it did do was to give me the first glimpse into the unglamorous backdrop of the medical profession. <br /><br />I would highly recommend this book for Pre-Meds and family/friends of future doctors. I came away from this book having learned a little more about medicine, a little more about the profession and a lot more about the struggles some people go through to pursue what they want in life. </span>
