<span id="freeTextContainer15686600161355608697">The story of what happens to people working 100+ hour weeks with 36 hours at a stretch with no sleep in life and death conditions. It&apos;s pretty terrible sounding, but good doctor in training stories. Luckily most of these rules have been changed by now--this takes place in 1985-1986. All these doctors were training in pediatrics (and this is set when I was a baby, so interesting to see what would have happened in my care--though luckily I never had any emergencies after my initial birth by c-sect</span>
  <span id="freeText15686600161355608697" style="display:none">The story of what happens to people working 100+ hour weeks with 36 hours at a stretch with no sleep in life and death conditions. It's pretty terrible sounding, but good doctor in training stories. Luckily most of these rules have been changed by now--this takes place in 1985-1986. All these doctors were training in pediatrics (and this is set when I was a baby, so interesting to see what would have happened in my care--though luckily I never had any emergencies after my initial birth by c-section). <br /><br />Only problem is that if you are pregnant in the third trimester, you will cry multiple times. Too many stories of stillborn babies for pregnancy brain.</span>
